============

Your subscription is paid to OpenAI.
Microsoft does not automatically receive a fixed percentage of every subscription.
Microsoft benefits through its investment, cloud infrastructure business, 
and commercial agreements with OpenAI, but the exact allocation of an individual subscription payment is not publicly disclosed.

============

You pay OpenAI.

However, OpenAI does not keep 100% of the money. It uses that revenue to pay many parties for different services and obligations. Microsoft also receives money through its commercial agreements with OpenAI, but it is not a simple "50-50" subscription split. The exact amount from each subscription is not publicly disclosed.

Imagine you pay $20/month for ChatGPT Plus

Your payment first goes to OpenAI.

Then OpenAI uses that revenue to cover expenses such as:

| Who receives money?   | Why?                                                                             |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| OpenAI                | Research, employees, product development                                         |
| Microsoft             | Cloud infrastructure, partnership agreements, investment-related revenue sharing |
| NVIDIA (indirectly)   | GPUs purchased by cloud providers                                                |
| Electricity providers | Power for AI data centers                                                        |
| Data center operators | Buildings, networking, cooling                                                   |
| Employees             | Salaries and benefits                                                            |
| Governments           | Taxes                                                                            |
| Other investors       | Depending on company profits and ownership structure                             |


==========

