| Microsoft cloud services   |             $6–8 |
| GPU & infrastructure costs |             $3–5 |
| Employee salaries          |             $3–4 |
| AI research                |             $2–3 |
| Operations & security      |             $1–2 |
| Profit / reserves          | Remaining amount |


These numbers are illustrative only, not OpenAI's published financial breakdown.

Does Microsoft get money?

Yes, but not because Microsoft owns ChatGPT.

Microsoft earns money in several ways:

Azure cloud services
OpenAI pays Microsoft for large amounts of cloud computing and AI infrastructure.
Investment agreement
OpenAI and Microsoft have commercial agreements that include revenue-sharing provisions under certain conditions. Those agreements have changed over time, and the detailed financial terms are not fully public.
Microsoft products
Microsoft also earns revenue by selling AI features in products like Microsoft Copilot and Azure AI services.
Does Apple get money?

